    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-21T05:43:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-21T05:43:00-05:00" n="728"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d728">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/10101</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BRC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-21T10:00:00-00:43">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 21, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 22, 12.18 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Legation informed that French wireless station here has been put in condition to
                    be again operated. Liberian Government has withheld its approval of this
                    procedure and insisted that station be immediately dismantled as its use might
                    invite another submarine attack. <pb facs="0839" n="747" xml:id="pg_747"/>
                    Replying French Chargé d’Affaires stated that station had not been operated and
                    would not be operated until instructions were received from French Government to
                    which he had referred controversy. On the 18th over protest of French Chargé
                    d’Affaires Liberian Government through its own agents took down antenna and
                    sealed operating mechanism of station.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BRC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
